%N A396259 Decimal expansion of the smallest positive root to 64*x^6 - 672*x^4 + 1764*x^2 - 1183 = 0.
%C A396259 Imaginary part of the Gauss sum tau(chi) = Sum_{a=0..6} chi(a)*exp(2*Pi*i/7), where chi is the Dirichlet character modulo 7 such that chi(3) = exp(2*Pi*i/6). Note that tau(chi) is a root to x^12 + 497*x^6 + 117649 = 0.
